  "prompt": "What NFL team has the most loyal fans?",
  "response": "Determining which NFL team has the most loyal fans can be subjective and depend on various criteria. However, several studies, surveys, and analyses have attempted to measure fan loyalty based on factors such as attendance, social media engagement, merchandise sales, and overall fan support.\n\nHistorically, teams like the Green Bay Packers, Pittsburgh Steelers, Dallas Cowboys, and New England Patriots are often cited as having particularly loyal fan bases. The Green Bay Packers, for instance, are unique in that they are publicly owned by their fans, and their home games at Lambeau Field consistently sell out. The Pittsburgh Steelers have a long tradition of strong fan support, often referred to as \"Steelers Nation,\" and their fans are known for traveling well to away games. The Dallas Cowboys, often called \"America's Team,\" have a large and dedicated fan base across the country. The New England Patriots have seen a surge in loyalty, especially during their successful era under Tom Brady and Bill Belichick.\n\nUltimately, the \"most loyal\" fan base may vary depending on the criteria used to measure loyalty, but these teams are consistently recognized for their passionate and dedicated supporters.",
